There are many off-the-shelf video controllers for non-gaming applications, from simple text or pseudographics ones like Intel 8275 and Motorola 6845 to more complex with many raster video modes, blitter, sprites, etc, like Yamaha V9990.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Thu Dec 08, 2011 10:20 pm</p><hr />
